org.gvsig.raster.wms.io.time

Class TimeDimension

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gvsig.raster.wms.io.time.TimeDimension
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RemoteTimeDimension, Persistent

    public class TimeDimension
extends Object
implements RemoteTimeDimension
    Class for WMS TIME dimension from a WMS. It allows you to handle the correct values for this kind of dimension.

    At the moment this class was written the WMS TIME dimension is defined as the ISO8601 standard for expressing times.


    As far as this class implements IFMapWMSDimension it uses the same interface and documentation.

      • isValidValue

        public boolean isValidValue(String value)
        Description copied from interface: RemoteTimeDimension
        Checks if the value represented as string is a valid value by checking if the dimensions supports it. It should be true if one of the following is true:

        1. The dimension supports nearest values and the value is greather or equal than the low limit and less or equal than the high limit.
        2. The value matches in one of the points defined by the low and high limits, and the resolution value.

        Specified by:
